This lighting control circuit is a basic interpretation of what will be created on a PCB board to integrate the power and sensing subsystems.
The primary purpose is to recieve power from the power board (12V) and GPIO inputs from the sensing board to activate or deactivate two separate LED lights in the porch/foyer.
This circuit was simulated and works properly.
As of the upload of this summary the PCB files are not yet available here but will be soon. (Approx. Feb 7)
